				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, my girlfriend and I go on vacation for 9 days.
<br />

<br />
Monday morning she walks into work, boss fires her.
<br />

<br />
The "other bookkeeper" has apparently spent the week finding anything and everything she could find to make my girlfriend look bad.
<br />

<br />
In fact, it goes beyond that.  There are now over $6,000.00 worth of "questionable" items and charges that they are looking into and telling her she stole the money and needs to pay them back.
<br />

<br />
They fired her and did not issue her paycheck for the month of July, as they are holding it until they figure out how much she should pay them back for any "questionable" items (and she had taken an advance draw for some of it).  In fact, they kept the paycheck and are demanding she bring THEM more money while they reconcile the accounts to determine if she stole anything.
<br />

<br />
Now this is a very large, reputable home building company.  And not only are they determined to break the law by withholding her check, but they are threatening prosecution for anything else they may find against her (who knows what this "other bookkeeper" might have done during the week, hmmm).
<br />

<br />
Anybody who has worked in accounting for a large company knows there are plenty of things that don't get coded property.  But why they suddenly think mistakes=theft is beyond me.  They have no proof that she actually stole anything, just the accusation of inappropriate use of company credit cards.
<br />

<br />
Yeah, I'm a bit pissed off.  Happy vacation to us.  The first time we leave town for a week off in years and look what happens.   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_wall.gif" alt="Brick wall" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I have all the checking statements, I know there were no other deposits made other than her normal income.<br />_________________<br /><DIV *****"position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=FF0000)"><a *****"font-weight:bold; color:#FFFFFF; text-decoration: none" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796  target="new-window"><b>Lord Zacatac Soulwanderer</b></a></div>"1450 Club" Tradeskiller
<br />
