<br />
Sure but employee is innocent until proven/found guilty...Plus
<br />

<br />
I am speaking out of experience as an employer. An employer cannot withold money that an employee has earned regardless of whether or not the employee is found guilty. The earnings must be paid because they were earned.
<br />

<br />
Even if an employee stole $1million they still must be paid their earnings.
<br />

<br />
The law states that whether or not the employee committed a crime that earnings will still be paid.
<br />

<br />
